attachments.text: The MDX-40 desktop SRP system can mill a wide range of low cost, non-proprietary materials including ABS, delrin, nylon, and tooling board. It lets engineers create functional prototypes to testing.

text: Following thoughts on 3D scanning for <@U0HPGQ4KH> 's bike, we can use clay/playdough to make a positive mold of the spot for the bike turn signal. Then we can use a cheap tabletop laser scanner to scan that surface to import into a modeling environment.
